  "response": "The amount of blood in the human body varies depending on factors like age, sex, and body size. On average, an adult has about 5 liters (roughly 1.3 gallons) of blood. For a typical adult male, this amount usually ranges from 5 to 6 liters, while a typical adult female usually has about 4 to 5 liters. Children have less blood, proportionate to their smaller body size.",
